vision-v1','','','2017-01-07 13:09:21','2017-01-07 21:09:21','',38,'http://transponder.community/2017/01/07/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(128,1,'2017-01-07 13:10:04','2017-01-07 21:10:04','<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-123 alignright\" src=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/admin-team-weekly-300x187.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"187\" /> Trans*Ponder believes that true change comes through A) supporting personal efficacy and activism within the trans/gender diverse community and B) supporting institutional change through training, and education. Trans*Ponder created <strong>Transgender Education and Awareness Services (TEAS) </strong>to fulfill our commitment to educate the community at large.\r\n\r\n(For a list of trainings, click here)\r\n\r\n(To request a training click here)\r\n\r\nIn order help create a safer environment for Trans/Gender Diverse people to thrive and foster deep allyship, Trans*Ponder offers local and national trainings to local businesses, state and city agencies, colleges and schools, health professionals and more regarding workplace inclusivity, examining bias\', customer service, evaluation of inclusivity policies and more.\r\n\r\nWhen we foster compassion, connection, understanding and safety between the whole of the community from within and outside of the trans/gender diverse community, we see many important things happen. There is increased investment from the community at large in the trans/gender diverse community, and a reciprocal investment from within the community outward.','Training (TEAS)','','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2017-01-07 13:10:04','2017-01-07 21:10:04','',38,'http://transponder.community/2017/01/07/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2017-01-16 18:55:43','2017-01-17 02:55:43','','WUO','','inherit','open','closed','','wuo','','','2017-01-16 18:55:43','2017-01-17 02:55:43','',49,'http://transponder.community/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/WUO.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(132,2,'2017-01-16 18:59:36','2017-01-17 02:59:36','Trans*Ponder hosts a monthly social gathering for the trans-identified, gender diverse, gender questioning AND\r\nour allies. This is your opportunity to meet new folks in the area, visit, hang out in good company, and get to know\r\neach other in a relaxed social setting.\r\n\r\nThe group will be lightly facilitated by two Trans*Ponder members. If you have questions or concerns please\r\ncontact the Trans*Ponder administrators at transponder.eugene@gmail.com.\r\n\r\n<strong>Age Limit:</strong> ALL AGES (13 and under require a guardian)\r\n\r\n<strong>Parking:</strong> Free parking in the Parcade on Charnelton St.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/SocialHourFlyer5.0.pdf\">Download Social Hour Flyer</a>','Trans and Allies Social Hour','','publish','closed','closed','','trans-and-allies-social-hour','','','2017-01-21 20:35:31','2017-01-22 04:35:31','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=132',0,'event','',0),(133,1,'2017-01-16 18:56:25','2017-01-17 02:56:25','','SH_Banner','','inherit','open','closed','','sh_banner','','','2017-01-16 18:56:34','2017-01-17 02:56:34','',132,'http://transponder.community/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/SH_Banner.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(134,1,'2017-01-16 19:00:04','2017-01-17 03:00:04','','SocialHourFlyer5.0','','inherit','open','closed','','socialhourflyer5-0','','','2017-01-16 19:00:04','2017-01-17 03:00:04','',132,'http://transponder.community/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/SocialHourFlyer5.0.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(135,1,'2017-01-16 19:02:54','2017-01-17 03:02:54','This is a monthly social gathering for the trans-identified, gender diverse, gender questioning, AND for our allies, 21+. This is your opportunity to meet new folks in the area, visit, hang out in good company, and get to know each other in a relaxed social setting. There is NO cover charge to get in, and any donations made go directly to Trans*Ponder to support the community.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each We/Us/Ours event is lightly facilitated by two Trans*Ponder group members. Activities may be offered during the event and you are welcome to participate or just be social! If you have questions or concerns during the event please seek out a facilitator or email the Trans*Ponder administrative team at </span><a href=\"mailto:transponder.eugene@gmail.com\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">transponder.eugene@gmail.com</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\n\n<b>Purpose / Goal:</b>\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hang out and socialize with gender diverse folks in a safe and inclusive public setting</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">HAVE FUN!</span></li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Age Limit: </strong>21+\n\n<strong>Parking: </strong>Free Pa','We/Us/Ours Trans/Gender Diverse Happy Hour','','inherit','closed','closed','','49-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-16 19:02:54','2017-01-17 03:02:54','',49,'http://transponder.community/2017/01/16/49-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(136,2,'2017-01-16 19:08:01','2017-01-17 03:08:01','This is a monthly gathering for trans-identified and gender-questioning folks. It is a place where we can socialize, share resources, and provide support surrounding the achievements and challenges we encounter from living the shared experience of being gender diverse. The Trans*Ponder meetings happen on the 2nd Saturday of every month. We do a potluck for each meeting so please bring a dish or beverage to share IF you are able.\r\n\r\n<strong>This group is exclusively for trans-identified or gender-questioning folks only.</strong> We do adore our partners and allies, and this group was created with a different intention in mind -- to provide a safe space where trans folks from all walks of life can come together and find community no matter their \"out\" status.\r\n\r\n<strong>Age Limit:</strong> 16 and up\r\n\r\n<strong>Location:</strong> For location details please email us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@transponder.community\">admin@transponder.community</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/TP_Comm_Supp_Flyer_v7.0.pdf\">Download Trans Community Support Group Flyer</a>','Trans Community Support Group','','publish','closed','closed','','trans-community-support-group','','','2017-12-11 13:26:57','2017-12-11 21:26:57','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=136',0,'event','',0),(137,1,'2017-01-16 19:07:45','2017-01-17 03:07:45','','Support Group LOGO','','inherit','open','closed','','support-group-logo','','','2017-01-16 19:07:45','2017-01-17 03:07:45','',136,'http://transponder.community/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Support-Group-LOGO.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(138,2,'2017-01-16 19:44:38','2017-01-17 03:44:38','<strong>PLEASE READ ENTIRE DESCRIPTION BEFORE ATTENDING</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/transponderpublic/\">TransPonder</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/gendercamp/\">Gender Camp</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Sweaty-Ganesh-Yoga-157325654298413/\">Sweaty Ganesh Yoga</a> are partnering to offer a by-donation Trans*/Gender Diverse Only Yoga class. Saturdays 6:30pm - 7:45pm.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Doors open at 6:15pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Please plan to arrive no later than 6:30pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Class starts promptly 6:45pm (NO LATE ENTRY - doors are locked)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCost is $5-$10 suggested donation per class. Please do not let price be a barrier to your attendance. If this is hardship PLEASE contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@transponder.community\">admin@transponder.community</a> to arrange for a partial or full scholarship.\r\n\r\nPlease bring a yoga mat, water, and two towels (one to cover your mat, one to shower with). There is soap in the shower but feel free to bring whatever you like to use. If you forget (or don\'t have) any of these items they are available in the studio to check out and use.\r\n\r\nNo prior yoga experience is required. All experience levels are welcome. The teachers are sensitive to community needs, are incredibly body positive, and meet students where they are. This is a Trans/Gender Diverse only class (except for the participation of instructors) in support of creating a safer space for a diversity of bodies. You are encouraged to use the locker room that you feel the most comfortable in. We acknowledge that there are only two due to facility restrictions, however, if neither locker room option suits you please speak with an instructor for access to a private changing area.\r\n\r\nPlease visit <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fsweatyganeshyoga.com%2Fpages%2Fyour-first-class&amp;h=5AQHSV07K&amp;enc=AZMt7du0SacHJzB8PuhWboX1ReA9u_v00vw6e9PXw_c0orxTuWi124hIA-Uta7WIte0&amp;s=1\">http://sweatyganeshyoga.com/pages/your-first-class</a> and <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fsweatyganeshyoga.com%2Fpages%2Ffaqs&amp;h=iAQEZNBUl&amp;enc=AZOW35wRD_ayO8vTBY8w3J4YJaMK_GrRGBkWFAPPyA8-BdvI7vED6foueRMwGXpe_gc&amp;s=1\">http://sweatyganeshyoga.com/pages/faqs</a> for important information regarding getting prepared for the class.','Trans/Gender Diverse Only Yoga Class','','publish','closed','closed','','transgender-diverse-only-yoga-class','','','2017-08-04 09:08:33','2017-08-04 16:08:33','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=138',0,'event','',0),(139,2,'2017-01-16 19:52:44','2017-01-17 03:52:44','Basic Rights Oregon, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/transponderpublic/\">TransPonder</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ppsworegon/\">Planned Parenthood of Southwestern Oregon</a> are pleased to present the 2017 Trans Health Care Forum and Webinar.\r\n\r\nYou will receive the exact location of the event in a follow-up email.\r\n\r\nOnce you sign up for the event, you’ll receive a follow-up link with the event location in Eugene, as well as a link to register at a broadcast in another Oregon city if you prefer.\r\n\r\nWe will provide attendees with an update on changes to the Oregon Health Plan (Medicaid); will discuss navigating the health care system, including navigating Coordinated Care Organizations (CCOs); and will talk about what’s next for Basic Rights Oregon’s trans justice efforts in 2017.\r\n\r\nCommunity members are free to attend, but the event will also be broadcast via webinar and on Basic Rights Oregon’s Facebook page. Please contact Dominic Lopez at dominic@basicrights.org to host the webinar in your home.\r\n\r\nYou can attend a broadcast of the event with other community members in the following cities: Astoria, Bend, Corvallis, Klamath Falls, La Grande, Lebanon, Medford, Monmouth, Pendleton, Portland.\r\n\r\nYou can view the event in one of these cities by signing up here: <a href=\"http://equalityfederation.salsalabs.com/o/35028/p/salsa/event/common/public/?event_KEY=3805\">http://equalityfederation.salsalabs.com/o/35028/p/salsa/event/common/public/?event_KEY=3805</a>\r\n\r\nThis event is generously sponsored by Wells Fargo, our statewide engagement programs sponsor.','2017 Trans Health Care Forum and Webinar','','publish','closed','closed','','2017-trans-health-care-forum-and-webinar','','','2017-01-16 20:02:26','2017-01-17 04:02:26','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=139',0,'event','',0),(140,1,'2017-01-16 19:54:06','2017-01-17 03:54:06','<h2>Meetings</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"meetings\"]\r\n<h2>Recurring Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"recurring-events\" limit=\"4\"]\r\n<h2>Special Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"special-events\"]\r\n<h2>Outside Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"outside-events\"]','Meetings/Events','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2