ity in Lane County Oregon and beyond. Oblio created Gender Camp, an annual event to support self-efficacy and community building, focused on the nuances of the Gender Diverse community. They also created the Rainbow Village, a LGBTQIA dedicated booth at the Oregon Country Fair, which serves 45,000 people over the course of its three days. They DJ Ecstatic Dance, a somatic healing practice, for a community of 550 people. They organize Gender Diversity Awareness Week, a week of events offered free to the community to increase Gender Diversity awareness, including International Transgender Day of Remembrance.\r\n<h2>Cass Averill B.S. <em>Board President, Founder, and Administrator</em></h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-60 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Cass-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /> Cass is a computer security specialist by profession and a transgender activist by passion. He founded Trans*Ponder in 2012 - a local resource hub, support group, and activist faction for the Eugene/Springfield transgender community. He is an organizer of Eugene\'s Gender Diversity Awareness Week and Transgender Day of Remembrance; facilitates trans* youth groups; organizes many transgender-focused events, and works hard to keep the “T” in the LGBT an active part of the conversation. Cass is also a sexual orientation and gender identity advocate in the corporate sector. He was the first person to publicly transition on the job in his fortune 500 global corporation, advocated for (and ultimately received) transgender-inclusive healthcare, instituted guidelines for how-to transition within the company, implemented all-gender single-stall restrooms, and continues to author and advise on transgender/transition related policies and procedures. He was recently selected as one of 200 (out of 3500 applicants) to participate in the White House LGBTQ Tech and Innovation summit. Cass represents Symantec annually at the Out and Equal Conference and remaining contemporary with what is happening politically for LGBTQIA people in the professional/corporate sphere. Cass works with organizations to provide gender diversity awareness training, policy and procedure consultation, and promotes the inclusive treatment of transgender employees and clientele. He holds a Bachelor\'s degree in Information Assurance and Security from Capella University.\r\n<h2>Seda Collier BArch <em>Board VP, Treasurer, and Administrator</em></h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/seda-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Seda is a trans woman who moved from Wyoming to Eugene over twenty years ago. She was the first transgender employee of the City of Eugene to transition on the job, where, in addition to her regularly scheduled duties, she has served on the Planning &amp; Development Department (PDD) Diversity Committee, the employee Benefits Study Group, and the Equity and Human Rights Board. While on the PDD Diversity Committee, she led the project that produced the “Celebrating Transgender Lives” display that is still used every year in Eugene’s Transgender Day of Remembrance memorial.\r\n\r\nSeda has been an activist promoting gender inclusion for over seven years. She is the Treasurer and an Administrator of Trans*Ponder. She has served on many Bridges panels (sponsored by the University of Oregon LGBTESSP) for university gender studies and health services classes. She frequently participates on panels teaching gender diversity as part of the Our Whole Lives (OWL) program teaching young people about human sexuality; sponsored by First Congregational and other organizations. As a member of the administration team for Trans*Ponder, she participates in Gender Diversity Awareness classes for organizations including Ophelia’s Place, the City of Eugene, Lane County Department of Human Services, Eugene Water and Electric Board, and more.\r\n<h2>Max Skorodinsky M.S <em>Board Member and Administrator</em></h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-95\" src=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/max-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Max  is a 44-year-old Ukrainian Jew and a trans man. Born in Lviv, Ukraine, he immigrated to the US with his family when he was 13. He graduated from a Jewish religious high school and later college.  He worked as a computer programmer for the past ten years, and is now a licensed high school teacher teaching at two Eugene high schools and the University of Oregon as an open transgender person. He works with local organizations to instruct girls in technology.\r\n\r\nMax started living as a man at the age of 34 and medically transitioned at age 42.  He is one of the administrators  and board members of Trans*Ponder and Eugene\'s Gender Diversity Awareness Week.  He frequently speaks on gender diversity awareness panels at schools and public service organizations. He helps organize the Rainbow Village at the Oregon Country Fair, an LGBTQIA dedicated space and resource booth. He has facilitated workshops at the International Gender Odyssey Conference.\r\n\r\n<h2>Grace Goodrich <em>Youth Ambassador, Administrative Intern, and Board Member</em></h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-96\" src=\"http://transponder.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/grace-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Grace is the youngest (and sassiest) member of the Trans*Ponder Board and Administrative Team. Grace is a Junior, and has held the presidency of Churchill High School\'s Gender and Sexuality Alliance (GSA) for two years. Grace is also the the Executive Assistant at Pierce Street Gardens, a locally run plant nursery.\r\n\r\nThey continue to explore their relationship to their personal gender identity, and particularly relates to others who are \"confused\" and exploring.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Meet Our Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2017-03-09 12:12:56','2017-03-09 20:12:56','',2,'http://transponder.community/2017/03/09/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(209,2,'2017-03-09 12:15:28','2017-03-09 20:15:28','[vfb id=1]','Request a Training','','publish','closed','closed','','request-a-training','','','2017-03-09 12:15:28','2017-03-09 20:15:28','',38,'http://transponder.community/?page_id=209',0,'page','',0),(210,2,'2017-03-09 12:15:07','2017-03-09 20:15:07','[vfb id=1]','Request a Training','','inherit','closed','closed','','209-revision-v1','','','2017-03-09 12:15:07','2017-03-09 20:15:07','',209,'http://transponder.community/2017/03/09/209-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(211,0,'2017-03-29 21:25:55','2017-03-30 04:25:55','','','','publish','closed','closed','','211','','','2017-03-29 21:25:55','2017-03-30 04:25:55','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/211/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(212,0,'2017-04-05 16:09:38','2017-04-05 23:09:38','','','','publish','closed','closed','','212','','','2017-04-05 16:09:38','2017-04-05 23:09:38','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/212/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(213,0,'2017-05-21 09:40:49','2017-05-21 16:40:49','','','','publish','closed','closed','','213','','','2017-05-21 09:40:49','2017-05-21 16:40:49','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/213/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(214,0,'2017-07-22 13:52:44','2017-07-22 20:52:44','','','','publish','closed','closed','','214','','','2017-07-22 13:52:44','2017-07-22 20:52:44','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/214/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(215,0,'2017-07-27 09:23:53','2017-07-27 16:23:53','','','','publish','closed','closed','','215','','','2017-07-27 09:23:53','2017-07-27 16:23:53','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/215/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(218,1,'2017-08-04 08:21:32','2017-08-04 15:21:32','<h2>Meetings</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"meetings\" no_events=\"Nothing currently scheduled, check back soon.\" showpastevents=\"false\"]\r\n<h2>Special Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"special-events\" no_events=\"Nothing currently scheduled, check back soon.\" showpastevents=\"false\"]\r\n<h2>Recurring Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"recurring-events\" group_events_by=\"series\" no_events=\"Nothing currently scheduled, check back soon.\" showpastevents=\"false\"]\r\n<h2>Community-Sponsored Events</h2>\r\n[eo_events event_category=\"community-events\" no_events=\"Nothing currently scheduled, check back soon.\" showpastevents=\"false\"]','Meetings/Events','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2017-08-04 08:21:32','2017-08-04 15:21:32','',44,'http://transponder.community/2017/08/04/44-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(219,2,'2017-08-04 09:08:14','2017-08-04 16:08:14','<strong>PLEASE READ ENTIRE DESCRIPTION BEFORE ATTENDING</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/transponderpublic/\">TransPonder</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/gendercamp/\">Gender Camp</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Sweaty-Ganesh-Yoga-157325654298413/\">Sweaty Ganesh Yoga</a> are partnering to offer a by-donation Trans*/Gender Diverse Only Yoga class. Saturdays 6:30pm - 7:45pm.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Doors open at 6:15pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Please plan to arrive no later than 6:30pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Class starts promptly 6:45pm (NO LATE ENTRY - doors are locked)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCost is $5-$10 suggested donation per class. Please do not let price be a barrier to your attendance. If this is hardship PLEASE contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@transponder.community\">admin@transponder.community</a> to arrange for a partial or full scholarship.\r\n\r\nPlease bring a yoga mat, water, and two towels (one to cover your mat, one to shower with). There is soap in the shower but feel free to bring whatever you like to use. If you forget (or don\'t have) any of these items they are available in the studio to check out and use.\r\n\r\nNo prior yoga experience is required. All experience levels are welcome. The teachers are sensitive to community needs, are incredibly body positive, and meet students where they are. This is a Trans/Gender Diverse only class (except for the participation of instructors) in support of creating a safer space for a diversity of bodies. You are encouraged to use the locker room that you feel the most comfortable in. We acknowledge that there are only two due to facility restrictions, however, if neither locker room option suits you please speak with an instructor for access to a private changing area.\r\n\r\nPlease visit <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fsweatyganeshyoga.com%2Fpages%2Fyour-first-class&amp;h=5AQHSV07K&amp;enc=AZMt7du0SacHJzB8PuhWboX1ReA9u_v00vw6e9PXw_c0orxTuWi124hIA-Uta7WIte0&amp;s=1\">http://sweatyganeshyoga.com/pages/your-first-class</a> and <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fsweatyganeshyoga.com%2Fpages%2Ffaqs&amp;h=iAQEZNBUl&amp;enc=AZOW35wRD_ayO8vTBY8w3J4YJaMK_GrRGBkWFAPPyA8-BdvI7vED6foueRMwGXpe_gc&amp;s=1\">http://sweatyganeshyoga.com/pages/faqs</a> for important information regarding getting prepared for the class.','Trans/Gender Diverse Only Yoga Class','','inherit','closed','closed','','138-autosave-v1','','','2017-08-04 09:08:14','2017-08-04 16:08:14','',138,'http://transponder.community/2017/08/04/138-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(220,2,'2017-08-04 19:48:34','2017-08-05 02:48:34','Just over a year ago. Trans*Ponder, a transgender founded and led community organization gained its 501c3 status to better serve the trans/gender diverse community and allies.\r\n\r\nOn August 6th, we will celebrate how far we have come, and brainstorm together where we are going as a community. During the event we will:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Share food in a potluck and socialize</li>\r\n 	<li>Launch our new office space and website</li>\r\n 	<li>Brainstorm ideas for our future</li>\r\n 	<li>Offer sign ups for volunteer positions with the organization</li>\r\n 	<li>Have an all gender clothing swap</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease bring a potluck dish to share if you can, and if you cannot please still come and enjoy the food and drink.\r\n<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">\r\nPlease bring your donation clothes as early as 12:15 to the venue. If you can help us set up, great! If you want to donate clothes but cannot make it this day, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@transponder.community\">admin@transponder.community</a> to make arrangements.</span>\r\n\r\nPlease bring your own bag to take home clothing.\r\n\r\nYouth under 14 must be accompanied by a parent. Small children need to be closely supervised as per our host\'s request.\r\n\r\nPlease park around the back of the building or on the 25th St side.\r\n\r\nPlease donate money if you can! Trans*Ponder is committed to keeping services no-low cost, and providing financial assistance to the folks we serve, and we depend on donations and grants to do this. If you want to donate and cannot attend, you can support us by making a reoccurring or one time payment here:\r\n<a href=\"http://paypal.me/transponder\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow noopener noreferrer\">paypal.me/transponder</a>','The Big Event: Trans*Ponder\'s Launch Party, Clothing Swap, and Volunteer Opening!','','publish','closed','closed','','launchparty','','','2017-08-04 19:48:34','2017-08-05 02:48:34','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=220',0,'event','',0),(221,0,'2017-08-08 07:29:41','2017-08-08 14:29:41','','','','publish','closed','closed','','221','','','2017-08-08 07:29:41','2017-08-08 14:29:41','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/221/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(222,0,'2017-08-08 11:18:41','2017-08-08 18:18:41','','','','publish','closed','closed','','222','','','2017-08-08 11:18:41','2017-08-08 18:18:41','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/222/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(223,2,'2017-08-11 10: