'2018-03-27 19:20:59','2018-03-28 02:20:59','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em>Minority Voices Theatre</em></strong><em>, in partnership with <strong>Trans*Ponder,</strong> present an afternoon of theatre featuring a staged reading of the play:</em>\r\n<strong style=\"font-size: 75px;\">Transfigurations</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right; line-height: 1px;\">by Eliza Roaring Springs &amp; Deltra Ferguson</p>\r\n\r\n<h6><strong>Followed by </strong>monologues written &amp; performed by members of the local Trans community</h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Saturday, April 7 @ 7:30pm  </strong></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Sunday, April 8 @ 2:00pm  <img src=\"https://d30y9cdsu7xlg0.cloudfront.net/png/497-200.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" /></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Very Little Theatre</strong>\r\n2350 Hilyard, Eugene</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>$5 - $50 sliding scale</strong> <em style=\"font-size: 11px;\">(no one turned away for lack of funds)     ||     </em><strong>50% of profits benefit Trans*Ponder</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em>For ticket information, </em></strong><em>visit </em><em><a href=\"http://minorityvoicestheatre.org/\">MinorityVoicesTheatre.org</a></em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<strong>Transfigurations</strong> was first written &amp; first performed in 1998. Reflecting the lives of Oregonians from across the state who identify as transgender, every story in the play is true &amp; told from the heart.\r\n\r\nWhen originally produced, it was not safe for readers in the play to be people who identified as trans‚ &amp;  in some cases it was even too risky for those whose stories are told in the play to come to see it.\r\n\r\n<strong>This will be the first time the cast includes readers who identify as transgender. </strong>\r\n\r\nTo bring the topic up to date, the second half of the program will feature <strong>monologues by members of the local Trans community</strong>, drawn from stories in their own lives.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Don’t miss this powerful groundbreaking event!</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Minority Voices Theatre is a project of The Very Little Theatre. For more info, visit <a href=\"http://minorityvoicestheatre.org/\">MinorityVoicesTheatre.org</a></em>','Transfigurations','','publish','closed','closed','','transfigurations','','','2018-03-27 19:20:59','2018-03-28 02:20:59','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=369',0,'event','',0),(370,2,'2018-03-27 19:23:21','2018-03-28 02:23:21','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em>Minority Voices Theatre</em></strong><em>, in partnership with <strong>Trans*Ponder,</strong> present an afternoon of theatre featuring a staged reading of the play:</em>\r\n<strong style=\"font-size: 75px;\">Transfigurations</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right; line-height: 1px;\">by Eliza Roaring Springs &amp; Deltra Ferguson</p>\r\n\r\n<h6><strong>Followed by </strong>monologues written &amp; performed by members of the local Trans community</h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Saturday, April 7 @ 7:30pm  </strong></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Sunday, April 8 @ 2:00pm  <img src=\"https://d30y9cdsu7xlg0.cloudfront.net/png/497-200.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" /></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Very Little Theatre</strong>\r\n2350 Hilyard, Eugene</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>$5 - $50 sliding scale</strong> <em style=\"font-size: 11px;\">(no one turned away for lack of funds)     ||     </em><strong>50% of profits benefit Trans*Ponder</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em>For ticket information, </em></strong><em>visit </em><em><a href=\"http://minorityvoicestheatre.org/\">MinorityVoicesTheatre.org</a></em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<strong>Transfigurations</strong> was first written &amp; first performed in 1998. Reflecting the lives of Oregonians from across the state who identify as transgender, every story in the play is true &amp; told from the heart.\r\n\r\nWhen originally produced, it was not safe for readers in the play to be people who identified as trans‚ &amp;  in some cases it was even too risky for those whose stories are told in the play to come to see it.\r\n\r\n<strong>This will be the first time the cast includes readers who identify as transgender. </strong>\r\n\r\nTo bring the topic up to date, the second half of the program will feature <strong>monologues by members of the local Trans community</strong>, drawn from stories in their own lives.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Don’t miss this powerful groundbreaking event!</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Minority Voices Theatre is a project of The Very Little Theatre. For more info, visit <a href=\"http://minorityvoicestheatre.org/\">MinorityVoicesTheatre.org</a></em>','Transfigurations','','publish','closed','closed','','transfigurations-2','','','2018-03-27 19:23:21','2018-03-28 02:23:21','',0,'http://transponder.community/?post_type=event&#038;p=370',0,'event','',0),(371,0,'2018-04-03 09:10:54','2018-04-03 16:10:54','','','','publish','closed','closed','','371','','','2018-04-03 09:10:54','2018-04-03 16:10:54','',0,'http://transponder.community/vfb_entry/371/',0,'vfb_entry','',0),(372,1,'2018-04-04 10:26:12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2018-04-04 10:26:12','0000-00