t=\"center\"][vc_column_text]Trans*Ponder is a grassroots, completely transgender founded and led non-profit based in Eugene, Oregon. It provides support, education, and advocacy for the Trans/Gender Diverse community and its allies.\r\n\r\nTrans*Ponder offers; several monthly meetings; special events for Trans/Gender Diverse folks and our allies; inclusivity trainings to professional organizations and businesses; and advocacy services.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_height_percent=\"0\" overlay_alpha=\"50\" gutter_size=\"3\" column_width_percent=\"100\" shift_y=\"0\" z_index=\"0\" css=\".vc_custom_1523132931955{padding-top: 50px !important;}\"][vc_column column_width_percent=\"100\" align_horizontal=\"align_center\" overlay_alpha=\"50\" gutter_size=\"3\" medium_width=\"0\" mobile_width=\"0\" shift_x=\"0\" shift_y=\"0\" shift_y_down=\"0\" z_index=\"0\" width=\"1/1\"][vc_custom_heading]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Calling All Trans / Gender Diverse Friendly Providers</h2>\r\n[/vc_custom_heading][vc_column_text]One of the most challenging things that members of the Trans / Gender Diverse community face is in finding service providers in the fields of medicine, mental health, surgery, and health &amp; beauty. Even allied service providers have a hard time knowing which other providers can help their Trans / Gender Diverse patients or customers. This makes an already difficult process more strenuous.\r\nWe are working to solve this problem by compiling resources here on the Trans*Ponder website and you can help. If you are a member of the community that would like to share their experience with a provider or you are a provider that offers a safe space and friendly services to the Trans / Gender Diverse community we are asking you to let us know. To get started, click the “Submit A Provider” button and fill out our provider intake form.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_height_percent=\"0\" ov